<div class="you-say">"The classification methodology has evolved to read a wider set of signals on each visit. Previously, it relied primarily on the referring URL. The new model also reads URL parameters, click identifiers, ad redirects, and session context. When a channel's share changes, it reflects this broader identification - the methodology is now reading signals it was not reading before."</div></div>
<p class="prose"><strong>Then get specific.</strong> If they ask about paid search, explain the multi-method approach. If they ask about Direct changing, explain the model now reads more signals before defaulting to Direct. Always connect the <strong>what</strong> (the number changed) to the <strong>how</strong> (here is the specific signal we now read).</p>`,
