{t:'"Where did the traffic go?"',isQ:1,
html:`<div class="client-block"><div class="client-says">CLIENT ASKS:</div><div style="color:var(--white);font-size:15px;margin-bottom:12px">"If my organic share decreased, where did those visits move?"</div>
<div class="client-says" style="color:var(--blue)">YOU SAY:</div>
<div class="you-say">"Each channel's identification has improved independently. The new methodology is better at identifying visits that belong in each channel. It is not that traffic moved - it is that the classification is now reading signals it was not reading before."</div></div>
<div class="callout"><div class="c-icon">⚠️</div><div><div class="c-title">Critical: NO migration claims</div><div class="c-text">Do not say visits moved from Channel A to Channel B. The methodology does not track individual visit reassignment. Each channel reflects a more precise count - that is not a migration, it is better measurement.</div></div></div>
<div class="callout blue"><div class="c-icon">💡</div><div><div class="c-title">Helpful framing</div><div class="c-text">Think of it like recalibrating a scale. You are not moving weight from one side to the other. You are getting a more accurate reading of what was always there.</div></div></div>`,
search:"where traffic go migration claims moved channel recalibrate scale"},

{t:'"Can I trust the new numbers?"',isQ:1,
html:`<div class="client-block"><div class="client-says">CLIENT ASKS:</div><div style="color:var(--white);font-size:15px;margin-bottom:12px">"These numbers don't match what I had before. Can I trust them?"</div>
